cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

This paper deals with motion segmentation in videos, which is a common problem in computer vision. The use of optical flow and probabilistic models suggests that this paper belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the use of camera motion and depth information suggests that this paper may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The probabilistic model and clustering algorithm also suggest that this paper may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the use of color features and video sequences suggests that this paper may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
